com.kuka.objectparameters

Interface IParameterStructure

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IBasicParameterMap, IObjectParameter, IParameterComposite

    public interface IParameterStructure
extends IBasicParameterMap
    An object parameter that contains other object parameters identified by their names.

    An object parameter structure always contains the object parameters as specified by its schema. The only exception are interface instances, which can be assigned to the respective key (as specified by the schema) via the put(String, IObjectParameter) method.

    The name of each object parameter is used as key. This map represents a mapping of object parameter name to object parameter instance.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        IObjectParameter put(String key,
                     IObjectParameter value)
        Associates the specified object parameter interface instance with the specified key in this map.

        This put operation may only be used to set the value of interface requirement entries in this map. Any other entries are fixed and may not be replaced. Use getInterfaceRequirementInfo(String) or getInterfaceRequirementInfos() to identify the interface requirement entries which are specified by the schema of this parameter map.

        This map only allows the object parameter name as key, so the key of each entry that is added to this map must be the name of the object parameter. Otherwise, an exception is thrown. Duplicate values are not allowed. If the map already contained the specified value, an exception is thrown.

        Hint: Use the factory to create new object parameter interface instances that can be added to this map.

        Parameters:
        key - name of the object parameter interface instance to be added to this map
        value - the object parameter interface instance to be added to this map
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with key
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified value could not be associated with the specified key in this map
        See Also:
        IObjectParameterFactory.createParameter(IParameterStructure, String, String)

      • getInterfaceRequirementInfo

        IInterfaceRequirementInfo getInterfaceRequirementInfo(String name)
        Returns the info about the interface required for the element with the given name.

      • getInterfaceRequirementInfos

        Map<String,IInterfaceRequirementInfo> getInterfaceRequirementInfos()
        Returns a map of all elements in this map for which an interface is required. The map consists of:
      • key: the name of the element
      • value: the IInterfaceRequirementInfo of the element
Returns:
a map of the elements in this map for which an interface is required
